s along the dorsal surface of the aponeurosis plantaris and extends to the level of the base of the prehallux.\" [AAO:EJS]\nis_a: UBERON:0010890 ! pelvic complex muscle\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (amphibian_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/aao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:3010693\nname: ramus posterior profundus of V3\ndef: \"In the adult anuran, this innervates the muscles levator mandibulare internus and longus.\" [AAO:EJS]\nis_a: UBERON:0004529 ! anatomical projection\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000375 ! mandibular nerve\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (amphibian_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/aao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:3010712\nname: levator mandibulae externus profundus\ndef: \"Jaw muscle which is responsible for the closing of the jaw.\" [AAO:BMZ]\nis_a: UBERON:0011648 ! jaw muscle\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (amphibian_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/aao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:3010744\nname: M. flexor antibrachii lateralis profundus\ndef: \"Originates on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus and inserts on the lower ridge of the radioulna.\" [AAO:EJS]\nis_a: UBERON:0010891 ! pectoral complex muscle\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (amphibian_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/aao.owl\"}